‚ÄúI am an unapologetically Black woman, who‚Äôs building a world where success isn‚Äôt determined by your zip code.‚Äù ‚ÄîActivist and organizer nupol_justice (Nupol Kiazolu)

‚ÄúBlack communities deserve equitable access to resources and a world where they can thrive without systemic barriers. My lived experience as a young Black person in an impoverished neighborhood inspired my activism. I realized poverty and violence are inextricably linked. I lost my father, close friends and many relatives to gun violence. When I was 12 years old, the killing of Trayvon Martin ignited my journey into activism.

Today, I strive to represent Black excellence as an organizer and DEI strategist, transforming my own trauma into a force for change, advocating for civil rights and supporting victims of domestic and sexual violence, as well as the homeless. Empowering youth to shape their own future is a central focus of my work.
